<text>Every city needs a tea place like The Loose Leaf! There’s parking in front of the building that I believe has a specific time limit.

I chatted with the person at the register and after telling me about the different types of teas, I went with Energize (which I definitely needed after my flight). Even though it didn’t have any caffeine, it gave me the energy I needed. I also ordered a flat white and it was tasty!

They sell their teas for a reasonable price and I love that they do their own mixes.</text><username>Diana Nguyen</username>< Pictures>

<userid>104362663643332457504<//userid><user_name>Bubba Boo<//user_name><time>1582422863069< /time>< rating>
5< /rating>
< Review>
It was my first time going with my beloved and at first we thought it was just a spot with teas (given the name) but they have deli food as well. We ordered a sandwich and a panini from the menu and the portions were amazingly big. We thought they were going to be smaller sandwiches and paninis but we were wrong. They also come with a side (salad or pasta) but the thing is the wait time can be a little long but worth the wait. We will definitely be going back, it has a comfy environment filled with mugs and they have tea flavor samples of the day. I would recommend if you are around the area.</Review>

I adore this place and their tea is the best. They put so much heart into every cup. Their ingredients are some of the best I have seen in a tea company. I love how they use organic good for you herbs in every cup.  They use some of the best healing herbs out there in their blends. This is a serious tea company with very professional people running it. Go enjoy a cup you won’t be disappointed</Text>

< review>
This was my first time at El Gusano. A coworker recommended we stop here for lunch.  It was pretty busy at noon. They are only open 11a to 3p so a busy lunch crowd was expected.  The inside was clean with nice decorations, sufficient amount of seating and music playing at an appropriate volume.  You can see the food being prepared at the front when you get in line to order.  We called ahead so we went straight to the register to pay and pick up. There were only a few people ahead of us so the wait was long.  I ordered the 1 item combination plate which came with a chicken enchilada, rice and pinto beans and a side of chips. Everything tastes really good but the enchilada is spicier than I anticipated.  I wouldn't mind grabbing lunch here again. Prices were great and portions are generous.</review>

<pictures>None</pictures>< Review>
We went with the signature/seasonal tasting menu which was listed as 7 dishes but we were pleasantly surprised because I swear we ended up with 12 or 13 total courses (there were quite a few amuse bouches at the beginning). Safe to say we left sufficiently full. Three of the courses were also dessert though, which I personally didn't feel was necessary. Overall the dishes seemed very thought-out, unique, and creative. It was a fun little  food adventure not knowing what was going to come out next!

My favorites were the fume of rockfish, wagyu cigar and black cod.

The two dishes I was looking forward to most were the scallop and the A5 wagyu. Unfortunately these ended up being on the bottom of my list but not because they weren't done well. For example, I've had wagyu a handful of times before but this one seemed much more fatty to me. I had a hard time finishing the dish even though it was 4 bites. I realize this is 100% a personal preference though and that other people love it. But if you're someone who doesn't really like fatty meat, I would not advise getting this.

I didn't think the ambiance was anything special/memorable but it was more lively than I expected compared to other fine-dining restaurants I've been to.</Review>

<Date>1545157327625<//Date><Review>Would give 5 negative stars if possible. Everything on the menu is sloppily prepared garbage and they don't even give you what you order half the time all while having terrible customer service.

Ordered chicken tostada salad and my wife got the Chile releno burrito. On mine there was a thick layer of watered down refried bean paste on the bottom of the tostada and all the lettuce in it was slimy and brown with gross hard chuncks of chicken through it, not tender and shredded. My wife's experience was even worse as she got a burrito without any releno or any pepper for that matter with the same nasty refried beans paste and hard chicken.

When we complained they said we could make it again but we'd have to charge again for the two orders but refused to give our money back for the disgusting food.

< text>
I have done a lot of research and have visited a lot of plastic surgeons.  I thought Dr. Alvani was too good to be true but he is legit.  A friend of mine had GREAT results and invisible scaring so, I was immediately interested.  When I visited, his staff was very kind and helpful.  Dr. Alavi was very profession, patient(important), and informative.  He makes it very easy to contact him with any concerns or questions.  Im so happy I chose Dr. Alavi.  The price was good for So. Cali and his skills (skill is very important).

Below are pictures of before and after surgery (2 weeks).  Everyone is going crazy about my results and recovery just after 2 weeks.  My scaring, bruising, pain, etc is very minimal.   My results were good from the beginning and seem to be getting better with time.  Patience is the hardest thing about plastic surgery but Dr. Alvai has great technique.
The left photo is my rhino/septoplasty.  The right side is breast augmentation and a slight lift on one breast.

I plan to update my reviews in the near future because Im always noticing  changes.  For anyone seriously considering Plastic Surgery w/ Dr Alvai, feel free to reach out to me personally.  I'll be glad to openly share my experience.   I love showing off my new body!! <3</text>

Rhinoplasty
This was the most amazing experience in my life for personal confidence. I just had rhinoplasty a little over a week ago from Dr. Alvie and I cannot say enough. From consultation to pre op to surgery it’s been incredible. My nose was long bulbous and crooked. I was just hoping for a nice improvement. I’m only a little over a week out and my nose is absolutely perfect. Better than I could ever imagine. From the research I did there were many stories of people having a lot of swelling weeks after and other side effects that are quite normal but time sensitive. My swelling is minimal already and not much bleeding or anything. I can’t believe it. I’m so happy with my little cute nose and it’s only going to get cuter in time. My experience was great. The staff is so warm and welcoming. Carol the nurse texts you before and after surgery to make sure everything is going perfect and reminds you of medication and other details of recovery. I just can’t say enough. I’m so happy with this. If I ever have any other procedure done in the future this is definitely my choice. Thank you Dr. Alvie for making my dreams come true. Xoxo</Review>

<Text>I came in for breast augmentation and had a good experience up to my two week checkup when DrSassan had found my right implant ruptured.

I normally don’t single out employees because a company is only as good as its employees so I will try to make my experience it as chronological as possible without mentioning names.
When I went in to my 2 week checkup it was with a nurse practitioner not the doctor. I commented I did not feel my right implant and it was much smaller and she said “well just push down the left implant” when clearly it was significantly smaller. I still didn’t feel comfortable and she asked if I wanted to see the doctor and I said yes. This is when DrSassan found the implant was ruptured. This to me is concerning because if I wouldn’t have made the comment or asked for the doctor I would of left the 2 week checkup with a ruptured implant.
Even though I got saline implants I was very scared and saddened by the news. This meant I had to do surgery again and take another week off work.
I was told that i wouldn’t have to worry about anything because it was so close to the surgery day and they would get in touch with me; that was a Friday morning. On Monday I still had not received a call so I called the same nurse practitioner and was then informed that I would have to buy the $200 insurance for the implant company to cover PART of the costs because the rupture was blamed on a defective implant. I was so overwhelmed with the thought of paying more and taking more time off work because I had already spent $8200 in total for my surgery. However I went ahead and signed up for the insurance just so I can get the implant fixed as soon as soon as possible.
Once signed up I called the same nurse practitioner at the office to schedule me in for a surgery asap. She said they would get back to me. No one got back to me even after calling daily for 4 days. Eventually I went over and asked to speak to DrSassan. He was very nice and empathetic as well as Sandra and we were able to schedule the next surgery.
However during that lapse I do think they did not give me the same attention as when I was a “new” client. I had to call twice for them to give me the prescriptions I would need for the day of surgery.
Everything went well after the surgery. On my SECOND 2 week checkup I had the same nurse practitioner. She asked if I was using the scar cream and I said no I would be Interested.
At checkout the scar cream was $150+. I said if they would give it complimentary due to my situation and the collateral inconveniences it had cost like emotional distress, 2 weeks off work and more expenses on medicine. She said she would ask the doctor and get back to me.
It has been 5 days and no one got back to me.
I called the office today to follow up because I mean at this point I’ve spent 8k I’ll pay the $150 to help with scarring.  When I called, the doctor hadn’t even been asked. They offered me a scar cream that was similar to the one for sale but a sample complimentary and i said yes I would pick it up later.
On my way there I get a call that that type of cream was expired. This gesture was so petty that they would offer what is obviously their least popular product. I wanted to be rude but I decided to ask they just give me a discount on the one they actually promote that is good and I would be on my way. They ended up giving me 20% off the cream.
I actually waited to write a review because something as little as comping the scar cream would of made my experience a whole lot better.
In CONCLUSION, I am writing this review as a feedback for your customer service. Sometimes it’s the little things that matter. I felt there was a lack of empathy and follow up from the nurse practitioner as well as the desk clerks.< /Text><GmapID>0x80dc00342f2eb8e1:0x9489814f86282f6b</GmapID>< pictures>

<Rating>5<//Rating><review>Before anything, let me say "YES"! Yes, I would recommend Dr. Alavi and I would go back to him in a heartbeat if I ever have another procedure!

I worked for a doctor who owns a successful LASIK practice, so I know what great patient care looks like. However, it wasn't until I had my breast augmentation by Dr. Alavi, that I got to be on the receiving end of that great patient care!

This was going to be my first surgery, so I was nervous for the initial consultation, but Dr. Alavi has a very peaceful and reassuring presence that can be felt as soon as he walks into the room. He makes great eye contact, gives thorough explanations, and patiently answers every question. His practice was clearly busy, yet he made me feel like I was his only patient of the day. He was honest and confident in the results he could achieve for me, which alleviated all of my anxieties. I was nothing but excited up until the very moment Carol, his anesthesiologist, put her special "margarita" into my IV. By the way, Carol is awesome! After 5 minutes of talking with her, you feel like she's your best friend. She calls you the day before surgery and sends text messages days, even weeks after surgery to make sure you are doing well.

ALL of the staff are super friendly. You can't pass by one of them without receiving a smile and "hello". Brittany, the practice consultant, was sweet and very pleasant! I felt no pressure from her to make a decision when she explained the cost to me. At Dr. Alavi's Office, it's not about making a sale, it's about making the patient happy. I've emailed Dr. Alavi twice since my surgery. Once on the weekend, and once during the week at 5pm. I got a same-day response from him BOTH times!

It's been 3 weeks since my surgery and I am already sooooooo thrilled with my results! Dr. Alavia was right when he said that if he did my surgery, it would be a home run! THANK YOU Dr. Alavi & Staff for making this wish come true for me!</review>< pics>

<UserId.>102320014444339011978<//UserId.>< Text>
Dr. Alavi not only made me feel like I mattered to him as a patient, but made me confident, feel beautiful, and be able to trust people in the plastic surgery field again.
To give a brief background of my previous, and first breast augmentation I would like to express that I was 19 and extremely vulnerable.  I decided to have it done with a doctor that I will not mention, in La Jolla, CA. I was a small, “Victoria Secret”, B cup and the surgeon recommended I get 450cc on the right and 500cc to have them appear more symmetrical. I trusted him after a few months of debating size and truly fell into what he thought would be best suited for me. Unfortunately that particular surgeon didn’t go over any precautions or how severe the change would be in my breast.
I moved from San Diego to Hawaii and my breast began to sag and take a toll for the worst. I’ve never had children, but it seemed as if I had breast feed a few. I was ashamed, embarrassed, felt so uncomfortable. My weight never passed more than 165lbs and my height was 5’8”, however my breast sagged a few inches away from my bellybutton. After 9 years I couldn’t continue to look myself in the mirror and feel confident. I had so much anger for ever getting surgery in the first place and at times would find myself crying over the issue. I decided to finally do something about it. I knew that I would travel to San Diego to have the surgery because in all honestly it was much more affordable.
I took the initiative in December 2017 to see the surgeon who performed the first surgery in La Jolla. In my own words he mentioned something along the lines that there was no way he would be able to correct the job he did.  He said,”Mark my words, no one will be able
to give you results close to what you expect.” It was as if he was also disgusted with the work he performed. I left crying the prestigious office in tears and feeling like there was no hope.
After a few days of searching on google, “Best plastic surgeons in San Diego,” Dr. Alavi appeared. I read over his reviews and was impressed. His work appeared to be perfection. Similar situations as mine, appeared on the before and after images and I knew I needed to make an appointment. It was so easy to schedule an appointment with his staff and didn’t take longer than a few days to see him.
My first impression of Dr. Alavi was his presence. His bright eyes, calm collective mannerisms, blanketed me with ease. He took a look at my breast and said this is not a problem. We can easily fix this. My mother that had joined me on the appointment felt confident in his tone of voice and how honest he was. Dr Alavi mentioned, no breast are symmetrical but we will do our best to get as close to perfection as we can. I almost felt like it was too good to be true. With how saggy my breast were and not to mention my right one deflated, I couldn’t believe I found a doctor that didn’t question the difficulty of the procedure.
My pre-op was scheduled for March 2018 and it couldn’t come any faster. We went over size and how the lift would take place. Dr Alavi wanted me to be a happy with whatever size I picked. He gave his professional opinion and agreed with me regarding going to a smaller implant size and doing a lift. The surgery went perfectly well, and I was static to
see the results.
I become emotional when I see the work he completed on my breast. I never thought I would feel confident, beautiful. I look down at my chest and I can not believe the magnificent work he did. My mom was left speechless. Dr. Alavi changed the outlook I had on my body, something that I never thought I would be able to feel again. I’m not exaggerating when I say this man is not only an amazing human, but wonderful at his profession. His staff took exceptional care of me from the very beginning till now. He truly looks at each patient as an individual. He wants to put a smile on patient’s faces when you see your ending results. I am forever grateful for Dr. Alavi’s passion for the human body. Thank you Dr Alavi!< /Text>

I went in for the consultation only expecting to get some basic information and I walked out with a surgery date. Their was no pressure from him or any of his wonderful staff. They all made me feel very comfortable in quite honestly, a very uncomfortable situation. Dr.Alavi was very patient with me during the initial consultation and did not once bat an ugly or judgemental eye at my son  while he was screamimg about motorcycles in the consult room. Everything was very straightforward.  I did not feel uncomfortable and I felt a very good energy from him. He has the energy of someone who loves what he does and he immediately gave me the confidence that he knew exactly what he was going to do to "fix" me. I scheduled my appt for a breast augmentation and abdominalplasty that day(I would like to mention i did lots of research prior to the appt as well and he still came out on top) The office staff is incredible as well. I would not have been able to get my surgery if Pat had not taken the time and been able to work within my time frame. His nurses and front desk staff are very friendly and respectful. He left a very thin scar. I  don't even feel that I had a breast augmentation because it was very painless and I cant even see the scars on my areola. He did everything EXACTLY THE WAY I WANTED IT DONE and I didnt even have to be very specific with him. He knows exactly what he is doing. I honestly couldnt be happier. The only painful part of my surgery was getting the drains removed(that part sucks). Obviously I have experienced some minor discomfort but that is to be expected with any surgery. I give him my strongest recommendation. So, in the interest of not writing an entire book on how satisfied I am,  If you are looking to have your life changed Dr.Alavi is a great choice. His rates are very reasonable and they offer different financing options if you don't have that kind of cash on hand. Also, they have a candy dish in the waiting room with good candy in it so thats just a little extra bonus lol. Go see Dr.Alavi. You wont be dissapointed.< /Text>

< Review>
I have been very anxious to come and write a review about my experience with Dr. Alavi and they staff at Center for Cosmetic Surgery... This has been a personal long journey for me.. Over the past 7 years I have lost over 160 lbs and I have always planned to have my girls "breast" put back where they belong and remove the extra baggage from my stomach..

I found Dr Alavi about a year ago, met with Pat had my consultation and was at that moment very excited... I was not only impressed with there willingness to answer every single question, but there willingness to actually work with me on a payment plan.. That was the only way I would be able to accomplish this lifetime goal.. So for the past year, I was determined to complete this within the year.. Well, I did.. my surgery was this past Thursday March 14th..  but allow me to go back a few days. the night before my surgery I received a call from Carol the anesthesiologist to go over my guidelines to follow for my surgery. Then she asked if I had transportation prepared for my arrival, and I did.. however; she offered to pick my up on her way in as she didn't live far from my house.. talk about amazing service.. That was a very kind offer as, I had to displace a friend from work to take me at 6 am..

So it's all set..The morning Of my surgery.. March 14th.. I was picked up and delivered front door service, Dr Alavi was there waiting, he prepped his artwork made his professional touch and advise, talked me through each move he was making and why. Then it was time. EEks I was so excited I could feel the butterflies in my stomach and not from nerves, from the lifetime struggle that I had been dealing with was about to make it's final move..

Surgery went well as I am here, don't remember much the day of surgery, however; I remember my sister wouldn't give me food or water until I got home :( Dr. orders due to the possible motion sickness.

Follow up appointment next day, arrived next day to see Dr. Alavi.. he is and was always right on time, I couldn't wait to see him and thank him..for doing this for me.. Thank you at this point wasn't really enough, until He removed my breast garment and my tummy tuck garment.. I have to say I burst into tears.. My eyes haven't looked down to see breast in more than 10+ years.. I couldn't hold back the tears, I had to hug him not once but twice, his abilities and artwork and professionalism to help me roll back the hard years gave me an emotion I didn't know I could have again. . I have looked at my breast or skin that has been sagging for so many years I Had no idea I would be able to see me actually have boobs again.. Then to top it off, wow tummy was smooth and flat.. there wasn't that inner tube of ugly fat flopping around.. Tears of joy. of a lifetime that has haunted me for many years is gone... .

I'm only a few days post op, and I am doing simply amazing. Sunday, I received a message from Dr Alavi checking on me, I was so thankful that I haven't been treated like just another patient, he actually reaches out to his clients.. it's a personal touch that I've never received from another Dr. in addition, I have to add!!! NO pain whatsoever with my breast or tummy, no problems, other than back pain due to stooping over.. .. I have to say I am very very pleased and overjoyed at this point, and I look forward to a continued recover and i will come back to keep all of you updated.. If you would like to follow me your welcome to look me up if you have any questions and or would like before and after pics.. I am keeping a log and will soon be able to show off the Mastery skills of Dr. Alavi... This mom can't wait. I would so recommend Dr. Alavi and already have a few ready to call for a consult, once there done taking care of me. .. He has been a blessing to me and my goals. I thank you Dr. Alavi and your amazing staff. Rhonda P<//Review>

< review>
My experience with Dr. Alavi and his colleagues, from consultation to follow up, was nothing short of spectacular. I had known for quite some time that I wanted breast augmentation and began my search for worthy plastic surgeons in San Diego about 6 weeks ago. Dr. Alavi was the first consultation I had. Him and his staff made me feel so comfortable and understood that I decided to book my appointment for surgery that day. Dr. Alavi spent time with me discussing my own personal goals and gave me insight into his own goals as a surgeon, which were ensuring my safety, understanding my desires and making those wishes come true. I truly felt a personal connection with the entire staff.

When I met for my consultation I had no idea of what size I wanted. I knew I wanted to go from a very small B to a full C, but had not idea about cc's or what I "should" get. After trying on sizers I thought I knew what I wanted, but was afraid I was going too big. I left the office with my first decision and didn't feel quite confident in my choice so I walked back in the office and they were happy to have me try on again. After a couple days I was still unsure of my choice, I wanted to be sure what I chose was perfect for my body, not too big, not too small. I was greeted again with open arms and his staff booked another appointment to try on sizers. I ended up going back to my initial choice, which coincidentally I am THRILLED about! Dr. Alavi has an eye for what looks appropriate and is best, he supported my decision and told me he thought I was making the best choice, really making me feel at ease about the entire procedure.

My surgery was 3 weeks ago and I could not be more pleased with my results. The days before surgery I was fully informed of what I needed to do to prepare i.e. what I needed to eat, wear, Rx's to pick up, etc. I didn't feel any anxiety because I knew everything I was supposed to and the anesthesiologist called me the night before to ease any qualms I had. The day of the surgery went very smoothly and the follow up visit the next day was a breeze. Dr. Alavi called me twice personally to make sure everything was going ok and to answer any questions I had. I'm not sure many plastic surgeons put that much care into each and every patient.

As far as my results, even only 3 weeks out with a bit of healing to do, I am 100% satisfied with my breast augmentation!! I will continue to recommend Dr. Alavi to anyone I know. Everyone thinks they have the "best" plastic surgeon, or say "I have someone better," but the reality is I went with my gut instinct and know I made the right choice. Dr. Alavi is passionate about what he does and puts care into each patient. If you choose him I know you will be satisfied. All I have to say is you're going to love your new look and best of luck with whatever you choose!!!</review>

< Text>
Some people like short and sweet reviews, others like details, so I will start off with a summary and below that the details. You can stop reading after the summary if you are a “short and sweet” kind of person.
Summary:
•	Exceptionally informative Doctor
•	Great Rapport / bedside manner
•	His work is meticulous
•	Staff is very helpful
•	Follow up post surgery is beyond what I expected
•	Both Dr. and staff and readily available to answer any concerns/ questions.
•	Excellent results
Pre surgery experience with Dr. Alavi:
Let me start by saying that I am a research fanatic, so when I decided to get my tummy tuck, I searched hi and low for months and months and ended up with a handful of surgeons I wanted to consult with. Upon meeting Dr. Alavi, I instantly knew I wanted him to perform the surgery. He was incredibly informative, had great rapport, and took his time answering all my questions in detail (unlike a lot of other surgeons whose responses I noticed where vague).  In addition, he felt it just as important to connect with me and tell me about himself and his work ethic. This I appreciated quite a bit.
Pre surgery experience with the staff:
The staff here is amazing. Upon arriving at the office I was greeted and made to feel comfortable. On my first visit I met with Pat. The sweetest lady who went over my goals/ expectations for the surgery, as well as my concerns, she showed me before and after photos of Dr. Alavi’s work. Above all, she had the most comforting demeanor. Needless to say, I scheduled my surgery on the spot 
Day of surgery:
It is clear that when Dr. Alavi is in work mode he becomes quite intense. The day of the surgery, I got to see this side of him that I was so thankful for, he was meticulous yet again with going over everything; he talked to me again about the details of the surgery, what to expect, how to take care of myself and gave me comfort and reassurance.  His anesthesiologist, Carol, then came in and comforted me before knocking me out. I woke up, got in a wheelchair and went home.  Can’t give much detail here since I was groggy 
Post Surgery Care:
Dr. Alavi had me come in the day after my surgery to check on me and make sure everything was going as planned. He later scheduled me for to go back in 5 days for another check up, then again after 10 days to get my drains removed, and 15 days to get my sutures removed. He then made bi weekly visits to see him that eventually turned into monthly visits. Note that Dr. Alavi will want to see you for a whole year after your surgery.
As far as my recovery, Nurse Cathy called to check on me every few days for the first week post op. Also, Dr Alavi called me personally to check on my progress.  She asked if I had any questions and how I was feeling/ doing.  Nurse Sylvia was the one who removed my sutures and she had such a light hand it was over before I knew it. She then discussed options for scar minimization and so forth. Again: super helpful staff.
It should be noted that every time I went into the office, I met with Dr. Alavi. When I got my drains removed (he actually did this himself), as well as when I got my sutures removed. This was very important to me since I had many questions and he made himself readily available to answer all of them no matter how trivial. He always takes his time and never makes me feel rushed.
My Results:
Even though I am writing this review 6 weeks post op. I can tell you that the results are phenomenal. The scar is healing very nicely and I am back up and running (well, at least doing some cardio ) I am so satisfied with his work and would recommend him to anyone/ everyone.</Text>

I am a young mother of two who was very unhappy with my sad looking breasts. I never saw myself as someone who would consider a breast augmentation as I was so scared of huge breasts that looked obviously fake. I am very conservative and was really wanting some natural full breasts to full out my curvy body. As soon as I met Dr. Alavi I felt so comfortable. I set my date pretty quickly and waited for the day. I received a call the night before where the anesthesiologist went over what to expect and to chat about my nervousness. I was ready! The day of-I was treated very warmly, like family. My procedure went perfectly and Dr. Alavi made sure I was very comfortable. My recovery time was faster then I imagined. I am so happy I found him! THANK YOU DR. ALAVI!</Review>

<review>I went to Dr. Alavi for a consultation based on the recommendation of a friend.  I've known for many years that I wanted to get a breast augmentation and was finally ready to move forward.  I made an appointment and kept my mind open to what I would hear.

From the moment I walked into the office, I felt welcome.  The staff at the front was very welcoming and offered water, coffee, etc.  I was brought back at my appointment time and immediately started talking with Pat.  Her demeanor and attitude took a lot of my nervousness away - I had never had surgery, let alone an elective one!!

After speaking with Pat for a little bit, she brought me and my husband to another room where Dr. Alavi came in and met with us.  I didn't know what to expect and was pleasantly surprised with the time he took to get to know me and what I wanted and what I was looking for.  He explained the way he works and how "OCD" he is, which is great, considering this is my body and wouldn't want anyone to just treat me like another number (which he does NOT do at all)!

I scheduled my surgery immediately with Dr. Alavi, I know that most people would recommend speaking with several surgeons, but after meeting with Dr. Alavi, I felt completely at ease and comfortable with him.  I knew that I could trust him and he would take good care of me.

The day of my surgery and the weeks after (it's been 6 weeks), have been wonderful.  The follow-up from Dr. Alavi's staff has been excellent, and I've even received calls from Dr. Alavi himself to check on me.  That is when I knew I'd made the right choice, the results have been amazing, but getting calls from Dr. Alavi made the experience even so much better.  Not too many doctors are willing or able to take time out of their busy schedules to check in on you, but Dr. Alavi makes time.

If you want a Plastic Surgeon who will make you feel beautiful with or without surgery, Dr. Alavi is the perfect choice.  If you want a PS who gives you recommendations based on your body type and not your wallet, Dr. Alavi is the perfect choice.  If you want to go to an office where you feel like you are an actual person and not another account number, Dr. Alavi's is the perfect choice!<//review>< UserId.>

< Review>
System Pavers San Diego is a 5 Star Company.
We first met with Heidi Dukefoss at an open house at the System Pavers Carlsbad office.
She spent plenty of time talking with us as we explained our project and what we wanted to have done around our house.
During the design phase she put all our wishes into a wonderful design for our back yard, patio cover, artificial turf, side walkway, front porch which included a ramped walkway, front yard and driveway.
All during the design phases she made recommendations to our project.
2 weeks before the project was to start we had a walk through with Heidi and the Project Manager John Parkhurst.
The walk through covered all aspects to the project and how the work would be done.
The project started on Monday 30 January 2017.
John’s work crew lead by Rafael arrived on time as they did every day.
The work proceeded every day and even with a few rain delay days they finished the work on 16 February 2017.
As with any home projects there were a couple of hurdles to get over and Rafael’s crew handled them with great professionalism.
Rafael and his entire crew worked very hard and every member is a real craftsman.
He made a few suggestions as the work proceeded and each one was right on and made the final product even better,
We give System Pavers and every member of their staff a 5 Star Rating.
And our highest praises go to Heidi Dukefoss Design Consultant, John Parkhurst Project Manager, Rafael Crew Foreman and his entire crew.

Donna and Gomer<//Review>

<userid>111832374141558154710</userid><username>Kristen Parks< /username>< Date>
1592276870695</Date>
<rating>3</rating>< Review>
I have waited a few months to write this review to 1) give System Pavers a chance to correct the issue and 2) not write it out of anger.

Our landscape install was completed by SP on 1/31/2020. From the time we signed the contract to the day the project started was just over a month. The crew worked fast, they were respectful, and cleaned up their mess everyday.

If you live in Southern California you know we had a heavy rainy season this year. It was around April that the sun decided to make its appearance and the weather warmed up. My husband and I noticed a melted strip of turf on our side yard. We had no idea how it happened. We checked our security cameras to see if it was vandalism but nothing was on it. We tried pinpointing the issue the next few days and as more melted areas appeared we realized it was our E grade windows causing a reflection on the turf and melting it. We put in a work order and our project manager came out rather quickly. He said that it was from the reflection of our windows, he has seen it before, and it is NOT covered by our warranty. Excuse me? We just spent over 30k on our backyard and less than 3 months of completion our turf is melted. Mind you we upgraded our turf in the backyard because that is where our children play. Call us naive but we didn’t know turf melting was a thing. As “experts” in their line of work our designer should have educated us. If not here the project manager who has admittedly seen it happen before should have educated us. Desperate to stop the issue we reached out to some window filming companies. We found the most amazing guy at RC Windows Films. It just so happened that he is on the board of the Synthetic Turf Counsel. He agreed that it is complete BS that SP did not educate us, did not offer a different design, and did not give us the option of a turf with a higher melting point. He even reached out to SP on our behalf to try to get them to work with us. He offered to send them a few thermometers on his dime that would be able to tell SP is turf melting will be an issue during their installs. We spent $1000 on window films. RC Window Films sent SP the pictures of the completed job hoping that they would fix our turf now that the problem has been solved and we never heard from them.
We also never received our $500 referral check for our neighbors two houses down using System Pavers. They had the same designer as us and she texted me Feb 1st saying she just met with our neighbors and put us down as their referral. Their yard install has also given them trouble. They had rain water flooding the foundation of their home. SP did come out and fix it as it was their fault. Our immediate next door neighbors were all set and ready to go with System Pavers until SP increased the agreed upon price by an extra $1000 with no real explanation.

That is 3 houses on one street who have all had bad experiences with this company. We live in a new housing development and our neighbors are finding companies with much better pricing and their yards are gorgeous! We definitely feel like SP is not in it for the customer relationship and just in it for the paycheck. I will say that our project manager was a great guy. He offered to come back on his own time and patch the melted areas with our left over turf at no cost. When he came back to do the work it turns out that our left over turf was from our front yard and did not match the turf in the back so we still have damaged turf. At least he tried though. It’s more than I can say for the rest of the company.</Review>

< Text>
We contracted with Systems Pavers for a 5,00O square foot driveway and we had a professional experience.  The sales person, Emily Kaye-Eddie was very clear about what is involved in demo and prepping before they hand-lay the pavers. She made sure we were aware of various financing options.  (Six months same as cash, twelve month no interest, or credit card).

The day after our driveway was measured and the contract was signed I received a call with the start date and a project manager.  Our project manager, John Parkhurst came when he said he would, returned calls within an hour and made daily on site check-ins.  He assigned a five man crew including a foreman. The project took eight days. On the ninth day Emily came by to see the finished project and check on our satisfaction. On the eleventh day John checked in to have me sign off on the project and to review care and maintenance. (Kitty litter on oil stains, round-up on weeds,).

Our large driveway looks lovely and is guaranteed for twenty-five years.   I sound like an ad because I can't  say enough good things about this experience.   In twenty years of home ownership and various home improvement projects this has been the most professional.< /Text>

< text>
We had System Pavers replace our concrete driveway several years ago. We were happy with the design, quality, and workmanship and were impressed by the time it took them to demolish, install, and complete the 1600 sq feet project in 3 days.

We have been thinking about a backyard transformation and front yard artificial turf for some time. We contacted System Pavers based on our past experience. We met Emily, design consultant. She spent a considerable amount of time discussing what we could do in our backyard, listened to what we liked, and gave us great suggestions and ideas. In a few days, she came up with a design concept that looked beautiful and functional on paper. We met additional times at home and at the showroom to fine tune the design. We found her to be so enthusiastic, friendly and professional. We were excited to start the project.

We met with Emily, Matt (project manager), and Rafa (construction lead) on June 20, 2016. Work started on June 21st, 2016. Those were HOT weeks in June and July, but the crew worked hard 6 days a week on most weeks. We had some change orders and challenges during construction but Matt was there to supervise and to address and resolve issues as they came up. With some of the features like the BBQ island and the spillways, his expertise really made a difference in the finished look and functionality. Matt is professional and great to work with. The crew was skilled and the workmanship on the pavers was exceptional so we would like to special mention Rafa, Miguel, Saul and Julian who we saw regularly for 5 weeks. The crew was also courteous and cleaned up at the end of each day. We also like to thank John Hanes who enhanced the solid patio cover design with lights and ceiling fans and his crew who installed the beautiful pergola in 1 1/2 days. The fireplace and lighting turned out really great. The quality of the turf is superior. The turf transformed the front yard and complemented the backyard hardscape.  Near the end of the project, the crew put back together things that had to be disconnected (irrigation) or moved (shed, dirt). Throughout the duration of the project, Emily followed up with us.

Having the 25 year warranty is another reason why we chose System Pavers. There are a few details to be done but overall the new backyard is now an amazing outdoor living space which we will enjoy for years to come. Thank you System Pavers!

Pam and Denny

< text>
My first encounter with System Pavers was at their display at the Del Mar Fair. I contacted them and discussed the costs to renovate my back yard. Their prices were very steep and I could not afford to move forward with this project. It was not until recently that I crossed paths with System Pavers again. They installed a brick driveway next door to my home.

The process moved along pretty quickly and it looks great, however I would not recommend based on my experience.  They set up their cement cutting saw adjacent to my property line and there was cement dust billowing up and everywhere. This left my vegetable garden and decks covered in soot which is so uncool. I spent hours sweeping, vacuuming and finally resorted to washing the decks to remove the layer of construction debris. They should have put up a silt fence or worked on the other side of the property which would have trapped dust. A west wind spewed their cement dust onto my property. System Pavers did not make any attempt to contain their dust or clean up the mess that they knew that they created.

An employee of System Pavers came to my home last week and I spent about an hour talking with him. I gained a lot of insight and knowledge of their business practices. I was frustrated about the mess that they leave and wanted to learn why they do not use any containment practices, I did my research and asked about several ways to control construction dust and why they do not use any of them. My first question was why they do not use a silt fence around their saw, he explained that the dust blows around it and it is not very useful.

We then discussed a special vacuum tool that would clean the mess up as the bricks are being sawed, but they have incompatible equipment and were not ready to invest in it. I then mentioned that they could position the saw so that the home itself would block the construction debris, but he countered that with the employees walking too far carrying bricks. I finally asked the employee about putting a tent around the saw and his next excuse was that  tents were not big enough. I have seen many large tents so this did not make sense and sounded like a cop out.

I brought the System Pavers employee into my back yard and showed him some of the debris that remained after hours of cleanup. He took photos of some of the mess and my contact information and promised to discuss this with his management team and get a cleanup crew out to my home. I never heard back from him after he left my house.

I have noticed a lot of good reviews for System Pavers and I believe it is because they report negative reviews to get them removed. If you look at their reviews on Facebook the numbers tell a different story. I want to provide detail about my about my experiences both as a customer soliciting bids, as an observer of their business practices, and finally one on one at my home so that they can improve and be considerate.

Please be nice to the neighbors and environment and insist on clean construction practices.<//text>

<name>L. Maria Stanley<//name><Date>1341977462237< /Date><Rating>5</Rating>< Text>
When we were growing up in L.A., I remember when the milkman delivered the milk, butter, & cream, the neighbors and the mailman was still white and Tapatio store was Better Foods Market, and I miss those days. We also remember the Hane's Hardware Store around the corner on Florence, then the Grandfather of the family owned & operated the store and was so good and kind to everyone; all people, and I will say this...this Hane's Hardware Store was the only business that stayed when all the other companies started moving out in the 1970's. But Hane's Stayed...and we all remember to this day who grew up on 73rd Street & San Pedro and the area.
Hi Dennis (one of the grandson's) I hope all is well with you & the family.
These have always been good people with patient and outstanding service to the community and the example of how to run a business. Continue the tradition boys, .
Grandpa's proud of y'all.</Text>

< Text>
Walking into Instrumental SB is a comforting feeling. It's an experience comparable to the feeling of being reunited with an old friend after a long separation. The warm smiling faces of the staff are welcoming and familiar. Sometimes, I just go in for the conversation and to enjoy the atmosphere. Marvin has never let me down, and the new guy Jacob always has a smile on. Fantastic place.<//Text>

Wow, great experience. Went in on a Saturday shortly before close to ship a wood working project. Fedex was going to charge me $170 for 7 day shipping and USPS only cost $70 for 2-3 day priority. < Rating>
4< /Rating>
< Review>
Typical post office. Bring your own mailing supplies as tape and other common items have a high mark up. Traffic is one through the parking lot which has 2 lanes: one that is for parking and another that is strictly for drive up mailing of small postal items.Keep in mind the same entrance for workers ans customers is also used for their vehicles and delivery of bulk mail, so only park in marked stalls. THERE ARE NO RESTROOMS OR WATER FOUNTAINS INSIDE.<//Review>

< text>
The post office boxes at Rancho Del Oro have been reduced from six boxes down to two. They are now often completely locked, as they were today.  When they are open they are stuffed and mail can be pulled out through the slot.

I now drive to Carlsbad a few times a month to mail letters. Letters send from my home might make it in two weeks to never. This began last year. I don’t understand why the US post office is being dismantled.< /text>

< Date>
1613868386346< /Date>
<rate>5</rate><Review>I have an immune disorder triggered from stress that causes my skin to get psoriasis so bad that it even keeps me up some nights and so I tried a few different cbd tinctures and lotions that have helped.

I tried edibles also and it just makes me nervous.

One of my best friends was diagnosed with C and when she started chemo I went to a few different cannabis stores. They didn't have much variety and every time I went I felt rushed by the staff and they were not very knowledgeable about what they sell.

I did some research and I found this gem. I liked the website and I could tell this business really took pride in there business. The store looked clean and they have such a wide range of items from topicals, tinctures, edibles, and my Much more.

I finally talked my friend into coming with me so she could pick some stuff out that would help her in her healing journey.

When I pulled up even the security guards were friendly they told me where to stand for social distancing but in such a kind way. It was my first time there so I didn't know. When I got to the window the lady there was very friendly also. When we walked in it was soooo clean and everything was displayed beautifully.

We were helped by Isa, truly a rockstar so knowledgeable and seriously educated us on a lot. Told us that what would work for my friend might not work for me. Also broke down to each of us what we should be the right mixture for each of us individually (she nailed it). My friend explained her situation and isa gave her a few recommendations. It was my turn and I explained about my anxiety also health concerns with my immune system. Isa knew exactly what to recommend.
I took home a tincture, some gummies and a cute sweater they sell with there brand .

I will recommend this gem to friends and family for sure. I think it's good for both recreational fun treats as well as anyone who need mor medicinal purposes. Also for someone like myself who is not exactly sure what I want or know too much about cannabis.

My friend said everything Isa suggested she tried and absolutely loves and so thankful for her time she spent with us. I tried the gummies already and love them. I felt calm but no rapid heart beat (that has happened to me in the past with other edibles)  :)  can't wait to try the tincture tonight.

Man I almost forgot I parked in front and the security guard even told me one of my tires needed a little air and where to go get it down the street. So kind of him

Five + stars for this business  and there fabulous staff especially Isa for taking her time with my friend during this challenging time it's so nice to have great customer service< /Review>< Pictures>

< Text>
This is a favorite spot for both local people and tourists! My husband and I went to Bali Hai restaurant before, which is Tom Ham’s sister restaurant, for the New Year brunch, we definitely loved it. So this time we wanted to try this one out. It’s right at San Diego Restaurant Week, so we ordered from the Restaurant Week menu. First the price is amazing, for brunch / lunch, it’s $20 for two course. I ordered Fish & Chips and chocolate mousse cake. My husband ordered Oysters and Lobster Roll. Both are super amazing, the foods quality and quantity are a hundred percent perfect. For drinks, both of us ordered their famous signature Mai Tai, it is a dangerous cocktail, super strong. One is enough for the whole brunch for sure. 😊 Anyways, we love this amazing restaurant, with the beautiful views and nice table service. We will come back soon!< /Text>

<text>What can I say, we loved our experience here. I was mainly coming for the view expecting ho bum food but we were pleasantly surprised:

Pros:

Staff was SO helpful and friendly. They even brought another heater out by our table to help keep us warm.

Food - we ordered the chicken and shortrib dishes. Short Ribs were so great and the Brussels with the chicken were to die for. Chicken had a nice crispy skin.

Ambiance/vibe: SO great. We came for sunset and looking out at the harbor with charming music piling through the speakers was just perfect. When dark enough their beautiful outdoor lights sparkled on. So charming.

Cons:
Chicken was nothing special and could have benefited from a thicker sauce or stronger flavor

Overall a 5/5< /text><pics>None< /pics>< resp>

Based on a friend’s recommendation, we came for Sunday brunch for the first time.  We made a 9:45AM reservation and requested a window table.  There was one available when we arrived.  We were seated promptly.  The view was spectacular!  Toward noon, the sun came though the window, so bring your sunglasses.

Service was excellent!   They were very attentive.   My champagne glass was never empty.   The finished plates were promptly taken away.  The buffet food was restocked frequently.   No complain!

Food:  the Maine lobster claws, oysters, cocktail shrimps, crab legs, and scallops were so fresh!  The cooked food and desserts were delicious!  Pasta and omelette station were very inviting.  There was bottomless mimosas (you can mix orange juice and champagne yourself).  We leave the restaurant satisfied.   One word summary:  yummy!< /Review>

<Text>Ambience: Pleasant environment, cheery staff, and the views of San Diego harbor and downtown are spectacular.  Even on Saturday night it didn't feel crowded.  Nice, open floor format with views from any table however the prime spots are outside on the balcony/deck.

Food: I had the special, whole fish (head, bones, tail and all) and I absolutely loved it.  My mom, dad, brother and sister all swiped pieces off my plate because it was so delicious.  The fish when I went was a Chilean sea bass.  My dad had paella which he enjoyed very much and my brother had shrimp pasta that he raved about as well.  My mom ordered a filet medium well (a sin in my opinion) so I didn't bother trying hers.  My sister had the chicken which was delicious with the bone in.

Service: The wait staff, food runners, and hosts were all very pleasant and accommodating.  It was my mom's 61st birthday dinner and she had an amazing time.

Parking: Extra kudos for a dedicated parking lot otherwise parking on the street would be a pain.< /Text><userid>100951041300598542773< /userid><GmapID>0x80deab0d284064d9:0xba249d609c190abe</GmapID>< Response>

Atmosphere here is really nice! We came here once before, for our 3 year anniversary and we loved it! We got lucky with outside seating and got a wonderful table looking out to the gorgeous view. Staff is very friendly and courteous, while service is top notch. The food is amazing. Hubby had the Cioppino, while I had the Lobster Roll. Both were very tasty with both of us loving the lobster roll. We also had the shrimp and corn appetizer, which was ok but kind of greasy and heavy.

This year we went back for our 6th year anniversary, and this time we brought our kids along. Once again everything was wonderful. And it was even more fun with the kids! Our 5 year old really loved the view! We'll definitely be back again.< /Review>

<UserId.>116503619246928386664<//UserId.><time>1524169100756</time><Gmap_id>0x80deab0d284064d9:0xba249d609c190abe<//Gmap_id>< review>
The views alone are worth checking this place out! At night come for apps and drinks and enjoy a view of the lit up city!

During the day, the harbor is a beautiful backdrop and tons of natural light bathes your table or you can even sit outside on the deck.

The food hasnt blown me away but it's ok! Hubby had a cheese plate that was fine and he shared a seafood platter with some friends. I've tried the ceviche and a cocktail (Saucy Sally) and they were both middle ground. That being said, the view is enough that we plan to go back to try some other plates!< /review>

The food was just ok. Not anywhere close to the type of taste and quality you would expect for the price. The service was horrible. Our waitress spent her time on the tables on both sides of us to talk very loudly about how much she disliked tourists. When she did actually wait on our table she was not friendly with us at all. We ordered oysters as a starter and ended up getting our salads before the oysters came out. She only acknowledged the error by stating she would put a hold on our entrées. Which we later found out that that meant they had already cooked them, however she just didn't bring them to our table right away. Food was barely warm by the time it reached our table. As a place that is a tourist destination with amazing views. You would think the server would have an appreciation for the tourists dollars. Sadly this was not the case.</Text>

< Review>
Updated 10/16/20:
Ever since I found this place, I've wanted to take my dad during his next visit. We went today for lunch. Gorgeous day! The downstairs patio was fully shaded with umbrellas.

The crab BLT was delish and large enough to share. The new style french fries are so dangerously good!  My mom got fish and chips and they were excellent. My sister got a burger, and she loved it.

Our waiter was outstanding! He couldn't have done a better job for us. My dad was so impressed with him (Roger). Our drinks were refilled regularly. He was friendly and knew a lot about the Destroyer when my dad asked about it.

Thanks so much for the amazing lunch and taking care of my fam!

09/10/19:
+ Made reservations, showed up, and superb table had been reserved on the patio for lunch.
+ The view, the view, the view!
+ French fries were excellent - very fresh.
+ Lobster roll filling excellent - very flavorful.

- They don't do anything to acknowledge birthdays.
- Hostesses were not overly attentive or welcoming; server was not overly attentive or friendly.
- Server didn't check in on food after it was delivered for quite a while, and we were missing an element.
- Lobster roll (bread) bland; it didn't enhance filling just muted it. Ended up eating the filling out of then bread with a fork.</Review>

<rate>5< /rate>< Review>
We were here for Sunday Brunch and it was awesome! Definitely come hungry. Maybe fast for 24 hours. I don’t know what you need to do, but whatever it is that will leave you with room enough to try ALL THE THINGS, do it! Everything was delicious from the pancakes to the crab and lobster and everything in between. As an added cherry on top, the very kind wait staff comes around and fills your mimosa glass the moment it looks remotely half full. It is well worth the price (but like I said, show up hungry to get all the bang for your buck)- what a fun brunch!<//Review>

Tiffany Bakel</Name>
<user_id>105297531304782191078< /user_id>< review>
I have been to Tom Ham's Lighthouse for brunch many times and I am never disappointed.  I leave happy and extremely full.  They have a variety of foods, such as the usual fruit, bacon, sausage and Eggs Benedict.  They also have other items such as fresh salads, meats, cheeses and lox.

However the highlight of my time at Tom Ham's Lighthouse is the Massive Seafood Bar.  This bar contains crab legs, lobster claws, peel and eat shrimp, oysters, scallops and ceviche.  Everything is so fresh and delicious.  The cocktail sauce is amazing and contains the right amount of horseradish.  BOMB!!

Tom Ham's also has a great pasta and omelette station. I recommend taking some of the seafood from the seafood bar, and shucking or shelling it all and taking it the pasta and omelette station to put inside of your pasta or create an egg scramble.

Tom Ham's is amazing and one of my favorite Brunch spots.  They take Walk Ins, but I recommend you make a reservation on Open Table in advance.<//review>

< rate>
3< /rate>
<review>The major perk of this place: The views, for sure! We ate outside on a sunny afternoon and the building blocked the winds, so we were quite comfortable! Our server was very nice and even cracked a few jokes.

I had to give it 3 stars though because the food was just meh. It costs >$50 a person to have an all you can eat buffet that isn't that good. We started out with the seafood--lobster, crab, oyster, scallop--and it was bland, didn't taste fresh or interesting, and none of us went back for seconds. I went for the eggs benedict next, and also found it bland. I guess my favorite dishes were the bread budding and the french toast, but I can get those things for much cheaper elsewhere.

For the view it's almost worth it, but I wouldn't recommend it ultimately unless $50 doesn't mean much to you.<//review>< Pics>

<Review>I took my wife here for our wedding anniversary.  I was looking for a place on the water, with a view, has outdoor seating, good seafood and oysters.  Tom Ham's fit the bill.  Beautiful view of the SD skyline, Coronado and tons of boats out on a warm summer evening.  They had 7 varieties of oysters on the menu, we tried 5.  All delicious.  I got the whole fish which was rockfish for the evening.  Normally I don't go for rockfish but I've never been disappointed with the whole fish and this was no exception.  I really couldn't get over how good it was and how perfectly it was prepared.  Tom Ham's wasn't on the top of my search results, but I'm glad I found them and gave them a try.  Oh, and the wait staff (sorry sir, but I forgot your name) was professional, polite, knowledgeable and right on top of everything. <name>Steve Johnson< /name>< Review>
Food was good, service was good. But, I had the Sunday brunch and it was the most expensive meal I have ever eaten.  After tax, fee, and tip I was out $70 for one person!!!
The seafood was minimal effort fair. All boiled, no interesting seafood dishes.
There was at least twice the variety on the desert table than everything else. They were very good deserts. But, for something advertised as a seafood brunch I was hoping for more variety in the main meal and considering the price, I was extremely disappointed I did not find it there.
I guess you are paying for the atmosphere and the view of the harbor.</Review>

<username>DiAnne Thrush</username><Time>1579824229313</Time><Rating>3<//Rating>< Text>
So maybe it was just an off day. We went for restaurant week we ordered from the restaurant week menu. They charged usfor bread for the table.  When I ordered the fried calamari and the lobster roll from the lunch restaurant week menu it did not say that the lobster roll came with French fries. I would not have ordered the fried calamari if I knew that there were French fries with the lobster roll. The lobster roll was not big and chunky but kind of flaked off lobster meat. At the end of the meal he forgot the desert.   The   cioppino did not have big chunks of meat but rather little pieces that were mistaken for potatoes.    The desert said it was a New York cheesecake which is inaccurate as New York cheesecakes do not have a gram cracker crust. The waiter was nice enough but once he realized we weren't going to be big spenders I feel that his  attention was being spent elsewhere... Over all it was a decent meal, the views are beautiful.<//Text>

< Text>
This place was amazing!! Definately has a lot of class, style and the sunset views of the city was beautiful.

My lovely lady took me to this restaurant for my birthday, it was the best possible location she could have reserved.

The food was amazing, i had an entre i can't even pronounce lol but it was the only one with lobster i believe. The lobster was delicious and the sauce really topped off the taste and flavors. It came with 2 sliced tosted breads to dip, scallops and clams. I am probably not doing the dish any service with my limited description but I'm not a chef so trust me when i say, their food is more than worth it.

The customer service was exceptional, the server knew everything about their dishes and had a very well creative and articulate manner in how to describe it to us. The wine was really good but maybe i could have chosen a white wine for my dish, i don't do white wine much.

Their dessert was delectable and just the right amount after a full entre. I had a cream brulee if that's the way you spell it, otherwise, my mistake, i don't feel like googling it or spell checking right now.

The view was really nice, when the sun is up you can see the ocean and the sailboats up close just underneath the patio or balcony seating. When the sun sets, you get beautiful views of the San Diego skyline. It is a great place for photos with a loved one, family or friends after your meal.

The food came out in a timely manner and the whole experience felt like this restaurant runs like a well oiled machine. I can't see why anyone would care to give them anything less than a 5 star.

I'd love to keep rambling on about this place but i got to work. Definately recommend it to anyone.<//Text>

[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPpHQ1U5PkUmdJ94pDp1UtlHMkMs_31V-iYKSA4=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//pictures>

< Name>
Zachary Steele< /Name>
<gmap_id>0x80deab0d284064d9:0xba249d609c190abe<//gmap_id>< response>
None<//response>
< Review>
Went here the other night and was beyond impressed. It has such a great and unique atmosphere. Most times with upscale restaurants like this you are left paying an absurd price for delicious food but incredibly small portions. Tom Ham's is definitely different in this regard, as the portions they give you are plentiful at prices that are absolutely reasonable for how well prepared the food is. I was also blown away by the prices of the cocktails for how good they were. The Bali Hai Mai Tai doesn't disappoint and the other drinks we had were fantastic while not being overpriced in the slightest. Also, contrary to other reviews on here, they do go out of their way to celebrate birthdays and are willing to go the extra mile to make that night special (cake and special seating with a great view for no extra charge). Perhaps this was a reflection of the server we had (who was wonderful), but every employee who we spoke with that night was also incredibly accommodating and friendly, so I don't think it was limited to that individual.

This is definitely one of the best spots in all of San Diego and I will absolutely be coming back for more of that asparagus and more drinks in the future! Can't say enough great things about this place!< /Review>

< text>
Beautiful view, came here for happy hour to take advantage of the $1 oysters. They were delicious and the view from the bar is worth the visit. Also tried the calamari which was average for calamari like any place really. The local beers are good to try $3 for 8oz if you wanna just try it! The bartender Joe provided great service and was very pleasant. I enjoyed conversation with him throughout my dinner. Would definitely recommend for people who enjoy good food and the waterfront. Don't come here if you're rushed...this is one of those relax and enjoy type of places, which you should :) I will be having my birthday here and looking forward to trying new things on the menu!< /text>

< review>
Recently hosted a luncheon there for about 30 people and reserved the upstairs private room.  Luz, our coordinator, took care of everything and everything was perfect - right down to our custom signage downstairs and personalized menus, neither of which were expected.  Our servers Sarah and Molly were on top of everything and helped us with some last minute changes (vases for flowers we brought, etc.) and volunteered to take our picture at the end in a beautiful spot with a perfect view.  The food all came out quickly and all at once and was all delicious.
I have been going to Tom Ham's Lighthouse for years and will now certainly keep them in mind for any event I need to host.
Oh .. and not to mention, I came in well under budget for my event.  5 stars for the whole encounter !!</review>

< Review>
I came here to indulge in the 3-course special during restaurant week.  A really good deal for only $35! The restaurant is in a great location on Harbor Island, with beautiful views of the downtown skyline just right across the bay.  We grabbed some outside seating so we can enjoy the view while the sunset reflecting beautifully from the buildings of the skyline. So pretty!! :)

The service was great.  The hosts were nice but our server was even sweeter.  He was very informative about their specials and raw bar menu.  For appetizers, my friend and I got calamari and mussels and both were delicious! For the main course, I enjoyed the clam linguine and my friend got the paella which she enjoyed just as much.  The desserts were a little tiny, but they were both really delicious and the perfect amount of sweetness.  I will consider going again :)  It was a great place for seafood.< /Review>

<date>1524340683543</date><rate>5< /rate>< text>
Awesome views, but also a great place to bring people who are hard of hearing—has high vaulted ceilings and carpet in the main dining room which makes it SO much easier to hear each other.  Most restaurants are so noisy & packed it’s impossible to hear, so we were pleasantly surprised even though it was busy we could enjoy the views, excellent food...and not have to yell!  Definitely going back.< /text>

< name>
Wendy Murphy</name>
< date>
1470252078975< /date>
<Rating>3</Rating><Review>Waterfront restaurant with magnificent views. I can imagine this would be a great place for a wedding or other big event. Waitstaff was friendly, if a bit on the slow side. We waited forever for our desserts and coffee, as well as the bill.Prices are what you would expect to pay at a semi-fancy waterfront restaurant in San Diego. If you want a burger for dinner, you will want to look somewhere else!
We were a party of 8 so there was a lot of different dishes ordered. Calamari and a platter of muscles was devoured quickly for starters.Two people had the Kobe steak which was good, but I have definitely had a much better steak at numerous (and less expensive) restaurants. Another had the Prime NY and it was tasty, if a bit on the small size for the price. The yellow tail and pan seared salmon were enjoyable and well seasoned. The bouillabaisse was a hit, as was the paella.
Key lime pie and a couple of hard rootbeer floats finished things off in a tasty and sweet way. The fact that anyone had room for dessert (very unusual for this group!) may give you an idea of the portion sizes of the dinner selections.
All in all I would say it was good. Expensive, but good. The real star of the night was the view, which was fantastic. So if you are looking for atmosphere to be the star, this is a good choice. If you want the food to be the main attraction, you can probably find better, and at a lower price point.< /Review><Pictures>None</Pictures><Response>None< /Response>< gmap_id>

The redesigned space transports the diner through the restaurant's history as you enter the first floor lobby then up the open spiral staircase to the main dining room. Staff are attentive and professional. The view is amazing from ANY table in the restaurant due to the tiered seating and levels of dining. The menu was spot on, fresh seafood focused. I'm going back!<//review>

<name>Francisco Meza< /name><time>1407252776917</time>< Rate>
5</Rate>
< Text>
I haven't been here for a while now, but I felt this place was worth leaving a good review.

There are very few places in San Diego that have a spectacular view like Tom Ham's Lighthouse. I used to come here more often.

You can sit outside on the balcony and have your dinner. Look at the menu online to get an idea of what they serve. I have never had anything here that wasn't good. HOWEVER, the last time I came (right after the remodel), the portions got smaller. I'm 6'1" tall and I had to order extra bread so I wouldn't leave the place hungry. The food is always great. I hate when I go to expensive restaurants and they server food I could make at home. This is not the case here.

Tom Ham's Lighthouse has started embracing the San Diego Micro Brew scene. You don't have to spend a lot of money to have a good time here. The bar itself is awesome to go to with your buddy. Bring a date, you can't go wrong.

I recommend the swordfish plate.<//Text>

<Text>Here is a good example of a restaurant that remains in business just because of its location.
We took our friends for dinner to celebrate their wedding and out of a few choices, the bride picked Tom Ham's for the views hoping that the food would be good as well. To our disappointment it didn't live up to the hype of people's ratings and was in fact quite a letdown on most items.
Some of the starters were acceptable but not by far on the culinary level that their prices would suggest. ALL of the main courses were below average and the desserts were simply a slap in the face. Just as an example, the 'deconstructed" key lime pie had the texture of warmed up latex and was served with a side of bright green goo, that not only resembled but tasted like it was made by Monsanto. Another dessert - the whiskey cake (also deconstructed) honestly reminded me of Von's cake from a box that spent a few days in a refrigerator and was revived by microwave to be served to us, likewise with a side of their signature goo, this time in purple.
Bottom line, if you want to enjoy the view just get a bottle of wine with some snacks and save your money for a restaurant where they can actually cook food.<//Text><userid>102330294009146773607< /userid><Pictures>None</Pictures><Time>1478537136208<//Time>< gmap_id>

< UserId.>
105521418723750750555< /UserId.>
<username>Carolyn Be< /username><time>1499111802106< /time><rate>2<//rate>< Review>
We went yesterday for their Sunday brunch. It was my birthday, so I hoped to have a nice experience. It started out fine with the hostesses recognizing my birthday, we didn't have to wait (since we had reservations) and were given a table outside with a fabulous view. I have a feeling that they failed to tell our server about my birthday, because he didn't say or do anything.
Service: Our server didn't seem to want to wait on our table. There were only two of us at the table, so it's not like it was a large party.  He said he'd bring water, but we had to ask twice. He said he'd bring more sparkling wine, but we had to remind him. He didn't bring a bowl for the seafood shells, though all the tables around us had one. He let all the dishes pile up on the table, so I asked a hostess to have a busser come to the table (though nobody did). I finally had to ask the waiter to clear the table for us. He brought a birthday dessert to the table next to us, but didn't do the same for me. I saw multiple bussers out on the deck helping out, but they would keep passing our table. Instead of waiting on our table, our server was busy taking cell phone pictures for all the other guests, or talking with co-workers. He never asked if we wanted coffee when he saw us eating dessert. He only came back to the table to let us know it was "last call" and drop off the check.
Food: There were only a few lobster claws hidden beneath lots of stone crab claws. The two pieces of lobster were good, but the stone crab seemed off (shredded meat inside with zero flavor). There was a pasta station set up. I asked the guy what kind of pasta it was, and he said there wasn't any pasta. I assumed they ran out, but he gave no explanation. Of course when we were leaving the restaurant, I saw him cooking pasta for someone. The short ribs were greasy. I only saw blue cheese, not a platter with lots of options. There was a sign for whipped cream cheese to go with the desserts, but there was no whipped cream. The smoked salmon was good. The ricotta pancakes were delicious.
I realize that this place is a local institution with a fantastic reputation. The view and weather were great. I've been to tons of local buffets, casinos, hotels, resorts, Vegas, etc. This was such a bummer. Especially, on my birthday. It's possible our server was having a bad day, but I shouldn't have to make excuses for that. We felt ignored, were extremely disappointed, and won't be back. The server makes or breaks your experience. I assumed the tip was included in the check, and that's why he made no effort. But, thankfully it wasn't. Gratuity should not be taken for granted, or expected if all you do is pour a glass of wine and bring the check. There are hundreds of restaurants in San Diego to choose from. When you are paying $50 for brunch, you expect great service.
PS - I just saw another review for the same day we went. He only gave 2 stars also. Maybe we had the same server.<//Review>

< Text>
Went there with our girlfriend for relationship anniversary dinner.

The place is beautiful and the view is wonderful! I highly recommand dining on the patio if you can, worth it and we were not cold. It was also very easy to park during week day.

The food was great. Maybe the soup was a bit salty to be a bit picky, but we were both really happy with what we ordered. The portion were also definitely enough and we had a hard time finishing!

Our waiter was delivering perfect service and was very nice. We were also offered a small chocolate cake as desert for our anniversary, really appreciated the attention!

Will defnitely come back and highly recommand :)< /Text>

<rate>5</rate>< Text>
Hello, view! My friend and I came for lunch during Restaurant Week. It was first time and I enjoyed the charm of the building and the beautiful surroundings. It was a $15 lunch menu which included 2 choices of 3 courses. I chose the ceviche and the lobster roll.

The ceviche, while tasty, was different than others I had. It had kind of a gelatinous sauce that put me off at first, but tasted just fine. The lobster roll was a generous serving of two mini rolls stuffed full with lobster and a side of skinny fries.

We both ordered sangria ($10 each) and it was the perfect Friday afternoon meal. Our service was great. Our server answered several questions we had about the menu. I loved all the seafood choices and the view is definitely impressive.<//Text>

<user_id>108100737183943161112< /user_id><Name>Jorgeanne Cabuhat< /Name>< Time>
1418666450299< /Time>
<Rate>5<//Rate>< review>
Best brunch hands down.  If you want to impress visitors (i.e., parents) bring them here.  It not only has a great view of the bar and city skyline but the quality of food here is superb. Plus for $42 a person not that bad for the fanciness.

To be clear, it's $42 a person with unlimited everything including champagne, coffee, drinks, etc. You get scallops, mussels, snow crabs, and lobster claws, which are all pretty big and fat. They also have an omelet station, bacon, sausage, eggs benedict, waffles, pancakes, french toast, short ribs, pasta, and prime rib. Plus a station of all sorts of desserts. But I stuck with the seafood station for my first five plates.  They were just addicting. Favorite was the lobster claws. Easy to de-shell and delicious with dipper hot butter.

Staff are friendly and they are on top of making sure your drinks are filled, plates and buckets cleared, and napkins changed.

Tips: Make a reservation and either request a booth inside or seating on the patio for an even better view.<//review>

<rate>4</rate><text>We celebrated a friends 90th Birthday on this dining experience!  We were pleased with everything the restaurant offered, from timely seating, reservation accommodations, our beautiful water-front seating!!, menue choices, the hostess, and our very friendly and attentive waiter!  The appetizers were amazing, the beer/cocktail selection was excellent, and our food was very good!  I am a very tough critic when it comes to food so if I were to critique anything on the cuisine I would say that the fish (I and my niece had the Market Fish, I believe was a Barramundi) was a bit over done and the falafel on the Vegetarian Dinner was a bit over fried and heavy, but aside from these issues both entrees were delish!
For starters, we had the calamari which was cooked perfectly and accompanied by a Honey Chili Lime Sauce to die for! < rate>
